requirementsQualifications:
In addition to the Basic Requirements for this position, your resume must also demonstrate at least one year of specialized experience at or equivalent to the GS-12 grade level or pay band in the Federal service or equivalent experience in the private or public sector. Specialized experience must demonstrate the following:
1) Experience directing the planning, organizing and conducting technical program analysis and development involving key agency programs;
2) Experience applying qualitative and/or quantitative methods for the assessment, development and improvement of programs and program effectiveness for complex management processes and systems;
3) Experience applying fiscal, contracting and administrative policies, procedures and practices necessary to manage and determine the economic feasibility of major technical and administrative programs;
4) Experience designing, developing and implementing automation technology initiatives with fleet-wide implications;
5) Experience with shipyard management associated with project management, human resources, financial management, manpower, material support and logistics support.

Additional qualification information can be found from the following Office of Personnel Management website:
